# Data Folder

This folder contains the dataset used in this project.

## iris_flower_dataset.csv

This CSV file contains data from the well-known Iris dataset, commonly used for classification and pattern recognition tasks.

### Dataset Description

Each row represents a unique iris flower sample, including measurements of its physical characteristics and its species.

| Column         | Description                          |
|----------------|--------------------------------------|
| `sepal_length` | Sepal length in centimeters          |
| `sepal_width`  | Sepal width in centimeters           |
| `petal_length` | Petal length in centimeters          |
| `petal_width`  | Petal width in centimeters           |
| `class`        | Iris species (Setosa, Versicolor, Virginica) |

### Dataset Summary
- **Instances**: 150
- **Classes**: 3 (`Iris-setosa`, `Iris-versicolor`, `Iris-virginica`)
- **Features**: 4 numeric (all float)

### Source
Originally from the [UCI Machine Learning Repository](https://archive.ics.uci.edu/ml/datasets/iris), this dataset is widely used to evaluate classification algorithms such as:
- Support Vector Machines (SVM)
- k-Nearest Neighbors (k-NN)
- Decision Trees
- Perceptrons
